This paper discusses the effectiveness of knowledge base embedding models for relation prediction and extraction, which are tasks related to natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper involves evaluating the performance of existing models and proposing a new benchmark, which suggests that it could also fit into the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with information retrieval and database management, which could place it in the categories of cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DB (Databases).
